The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, administered the oath of office to Senator Dan Coats, who became the fifth Director of National Intelligence for the United States. Pence praised Coats for his long career in public service and his commitment to the safety and security of the American people. Coats expressed his gratitude for the opportunity to lead the intelligence community and emphasized the importance of providing the President and policymakers with the necessary information to make informed decisions.